"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-09-17-jordan-chiles-appeals-unfair-olympics-bronze-medal-decision\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Team USA gymnast Jordan Chiles is still fighting to get herbronze medalback.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 76, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 8, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9990177712148522, \"rank\": 0.0006394923297818919, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 17, \"end\": 30, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"herbronze medalback\", \"from\": 56, \"to\": 75}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympian filed an appeal of the decision that saw the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS) force her to cede her third-place title in the floor event to Ana B\\u00c4\\u0083rbosu of Romania, per an announcement made by her attorneys on Monday.\\u00c2 Chiles is now appealing the decision in Switzerland, where CAS is headquartered.\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cFrom start to finish, the procedures leading to the CAS panel\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s decision were fundamentally unfair, and it is no surprise that they resulted in an unjust decision,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the athlete's lawyers said in a statement,per CNN.\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cChiles believes in competing fairly and with integrity and holding these organizations to the standards and rules that were established to ensure fairness,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Chiles' legal team continued.\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cJordan Chiles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 appeals present the international community with an easy legal question\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094will everyone stand by while an Olympic athlete who has done only the right thing is stripped of her medal because of fundamental unfairness in an ad-hoc arbitration process?\", \"from\": 78, \"to\": 1090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 82, \"end\": 87, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999996779852791, \"rank\": 3.220157602436451e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 88, \"end\": 96, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999925223619, \"rank\": 7.477643467148073e-09, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 257, \"end\": 264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.9988440159596347, \"rank\": 0.0010081640979546364, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}, {\"begin\": 361, \"end\": 372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9994378828194984, \"rank\": 0.0005602349687031698, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 380, \"end\": 383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0952711162608306e-21, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 459, \"end\": 462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0952711162608306e-21, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http: